item.description:
wasabibot:

Want to switch from Virtualbox to KVM

wasabibot:

Note: I am posting this from virtualbox whonix

Tor reports: WARN BOOTSTRAP PROGRESS=5 TAG=conn SUMMARY=“Connecting to a relay” WARNING=“No route to host” REASON=NOROUTE COUNT=17 RECOMMENDATION=warn HOSTID=“BCEDF6C193AA687AE471B8A22EBF6BC57C2D285E” HOSTADDR=“198.96.155.3:5001”

Parallel installation of VirtualBox and KVM at the same time is either difficult or impossible. Leftovers of VirtualBox might break KVM (networking or everything) and vice versa.

This is more likely a general KVM installation issue rather than Whonix issue. To fix this, you’d have to make sure that networking is functional in KVM VMs generally before using Whonix.

Read full topic
